# TUI / CLI registry — consumed by the `tui` zsh function (see ../conf/zsh/zshrc).
# Format: TOOL|CATEGORY|DESCRIPTION
# - TOOL must match a binary in PATH (or `nvim:<thing>` for nvim-only entries).
# - CATEGORY is freeform but kept short (used as column in fzf).
# - DESCRIPTION is shown next to the tool name.
# Lines starting with `#` and empty lines are ignored.
# The fzf preview reads ../cheatsheets/<TOOL>.md (if present).

gitui|git|Standalone git TUI (Rust, vim keys)
posting|http|HTTP client TUI (Postman replacement candidate)
btop|sys|System dashboard (CPU/RAM/net/proc)
btm|sys|Lightweight system monitor (bottom)
procs|sys|Process tree with color (htop-like)
dust|fs|Disk usage tree
yazi|fs|File manager with previews
lazydocker|docker|Docker containers / compose TUI
atuin|shell|Shell history TUI (also Ctrl+R)
fx|json|Interactive JSON viewer
glow|markdown|Markdown reader
arttime|misc|ASCII art clock / pomodoro
nvim:neogit|git|Open Neovim and launch :Neogit
hyperfine|bench|Statistical command benchmarking (interactive prompt)
glab|gitlab|GitLab CLI (MR / CI / issues)
glab-pick|gitlab|GitLab fzf hub (gp — project → MR / CI)
difft|git|Structural diff (AST-aware); prefer `git dft` from a repo
tokei|stats|Count lines of code by language
tldr|docs|Community man pages (tlrc)
